{"title_page": "Dave Gettleman", "text_new": "{{short description|American football general manager}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Dave Gettleman\n| image               = <!-- Only free-content images are allowed for depicting living people -- see [[WP:NONFREE]]. -->\n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| current_team        = New York Giants\n| position            = General manager\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1951|2|21|mf=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Boston, Massachusetts]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| high_school         = [[Boston Latin School|Boston Latin]]\n| college             = [[Squidward Community College]]\n| pastadmin           = \n* [[Buffalo Bills]] ({{NFL Year|1986}}) <br> Scouting intern\n* [[Buffalo Bills]] ({{NFL Year|1987}}\u2013{{NFL Year|1993}}) <br> Scout\n* [[Denver Broncos]] ({{NFL Year|1994}}\u2013{{NFL Year|1997}}) <br> Scout\n* [[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|1998}}) <br> Scout\n| pastexecutive       = \n* [[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|1999}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2011}}) <br> Pro personnel director\n* [[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|2012}}) <br> Senior pro personnel analyst\n* [[Carolina Panthers]] ({{NFL Year|2013}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2017}}) <br> General manager\n* [[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|2018}}\u2013present) <br> General manager\n| highlights          = \n;As executive\n* 2\u00d7 [[Super Bowl]] champion ([[Super Bowl XLII|XLII]], [[Super Bowl XLVI|XLVI]])\n;As administrator\n* Super Bowl champion ([[Super Bowl XXXII|XXXII]])\n}}\n\n'''David Alan Gettleman''' (born February 21, 1951) is an [[American football]] executive who is the [[General manager (American football)|general manager]] for the [[New York Giants]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He was previously the general manager of the [[Carolina Panthers]].\n\n==Early life and education==\nGettleman grew up in the [[Mattapan]] neighborhood of [[Boston, Massachusetts]]. He attended [[Boston Latin School]], where he played varsity football. He then attended [[Squidward Community College]], where he earned a degree in Clowning and played QuarterBack on the freshman football team. Gettleman has two master's degrees: one in physical education from [[Southern Connecticut State]] in 1978, and another in sports administration from [[St. Thomas University (Florida)|St. Thomas University]] in 1986.\n\n==Football career==\n===Coaching===\nHe began his football career as a teacher-coach at [[Spackenkill High School]] in [[Poughkeepsie, New York]]. As the head coach from 1973\u201378 and 1980\u201381, Gettleman led his teams to two league titles, competing against schools twice the size as Spackenkill. He spent a season as a volunteer assistant at [[Cal State Long Beach]] in 1979. Gettleman joined the faculty of Kingston High School in 1982 and became the head coach in 1984, leading his team to a Section I Bowl berth. \n\n===Front office===\nHe entered the NFL in 1986 as a scouting intern for the [[Buffalo Bills]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/8829025/carolina-panthers-name-dave-gettleman-general-manager |title=Panthers name Dave Gettleman GM |date=January 10, 2013 |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=April 12, 2013}}</ref> He spent the next seven years working in their scouting department before leaving to accept a scouting job with the [[Denver Broncos]] after the 1993 season. In 1998, he was hired by the [[New York Giants]], who promoted him to Pro Personnel Director the next year. In 2012, he was given the title of Senior Pro Personnel Analyst. \n\nIn January 2013, he was chosen to become the General Manager of the Carolina Panthers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/2013/01/09/3775378/bio-panthers-general-manager-dave.html |title=Bio: Panthers general manager Dave Gettleman |date=January 9, 2013 |publisher=The Charlotte Observer |accessdate=April 12, 2013 }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In the 2015 season, the Panthers reached [[Super Bowl 50]] on February 7, 2016. The Panthers fell to the [[2015 Denver Broncos season|Denver Broncos]] by a score of 24\u201310.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/201602070den.htm|title=Super Bowl 50 - Denver Broncos vs. Carolina Panthers - February 7th, 2016|work=[[Pro-Football-Reference.com]]|accessdate=August 7, 2017}}</ref> On July 17, 2017, the Panthers relieved him of his duties as General Manager.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2722139-dave-gettleman-relieved-of-gm-duties-by-panthers-owner-jerry-richardson |title=Dave Gettleman Relieved of GM Duties by Panthers Owner Jerry Richardson |publisher=Bleacher Report |accessdate=July 17, 2017}}</ref> During Gettleman's tenure as General Manager the Panthers compiled a regular season record of 51-28-1. In that 5-year timeframe the Panthers advanced to the playoffs 4 seasons and won 3 NFC South titles.\n\n===Return to the Giants (2017-present)===\nOn December 28, 2017, Gettleman was named as the new general manager of the New York Giants, returning to the Giants fold after six years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.giants.com/news-and-blogs/article-1/Giants-hire-Dave-Gettleman-as-General-Manager-/f780fe98-f0ec-4cdc-b6fb-4a896a9039e4|title=Giants hire Dave Gettleman as General Manager|access-date=December 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGettleman is a [[Messianic Judaism|Messianic Jew]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://billygraham.org/story/carolina-panthers-general-manager-finds-peace-in-christ/ | title=Carolina Panthers\u2019 General Manager Finds Peace in Christ | publisher=Billy Graham Evangelistic Association | accessdate=4 April 2019}}</ref> On June 5, 2018 it was announced Gettleman would undergo treatment for [[lymphoma]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000935835/article/giants-gm-dave-gettleman-diagnosed-with-lymphoma|title=Giants GM Dave Gettleman diagnosed with lymphoma|website=NFL.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.giants.com/team/staff/dave-gettleman/88ad57b9-fdc9-4d07-8fc0-6fa594e64c6e New York Giants profile]\n\n{{NFL general manager navbox}}\n{{New York Giants}}\n{{Carolina Panthers general manager navbox}}\n{{New York Giants general manager navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gettleman, Dave}}\n[[Category:Carolina Panthers executives]]\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Denver Broncos scouts]]\n[[Category:New York Giants scouts]]\n[[Category:Buffalo Bills scouts]]\n[[Category:New York Giants executives]]\n[[Category:American football offensive tackles]]\n[[Category:Messianic Jews]]\n[[Category:Springfield Pride football players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Boston]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:High school football coaches in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:People from Mattapan]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American football general manager}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Dave Gettleman\n| image               = <!-- Only free-content images are allowed for depicting living people -- see [[WP:NONFREE]]. -->\n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| current_team        = New York Giants\n| position            = General manager\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1951|2|21|mf=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Boston, Massachusetts]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| high_school         = [[Boston Latin School|Boston Latin]]\n| college             = [[Springfield College (Massachusetts)|Springfield]]\n| pastadmin           = \n* [[Buffalo Bills]] ({{NFL Year|1986}}) <br> Scouting intern\n* [[Buffalo Bills]] ({{NFL Year|1987}}\u2013{{NFL Year|1993}}) <br> Scout\n* [[Denver Broncos]] ({{NFL Year|1994}}\u2013{{NFL Year|1997}}) <br> Scout\n* [[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|1998}}) <br> Scout\n| pastexecutive       = \n* [[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|1999}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2011}}) <br> Pro personnel director\n* [[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|2012}}) <br> Senior pro personnel analyst\n* [[Carolina Panthers]] ({{NFL Year|2013}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2017}}) <br> General manager\n* [[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|2018}}\u2013present) <br> General manager\n| highlights          = \n;As executive\n* 2\u00d7 [[Super Bowl]] champion ([[Super Bowl XLII|XLII]], [[Super Bowl XLVI|XLVI]])\n;As administrator\n* Super Bowl champion ([[Super Bowl XXXII|XXXII]])\n}}\n\n'''David Alan Gettleman''' (born February 21, 1951) is an [[American football]] executive who is the [[General manager (American football)|general manager]] for the [[New York Giants]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He was previously the general manager of the [[Carolina Panthers]].\n\n==Early life and education==\nGettleman grew up in the [[Mattapan]] neighborhood of [[Boston, Massachusetts]]. He attended [[Boston Latin School]], where he played varsity football. He then attended [[Springfield College]], where he earned a degree in education and played offensive tackle on the freshman football team. Gettleman has two master's degrees: one in physical education from [[Southern Connecticut State]] in 1978, and another in sports administration from [[St. Thomas University (Florida)|St. Thomas University]] in 1986.\n\n==Football career==\n===Coaching===\nHe began his football career as a teacher-coach at [[Spackenkill High School]] in [[Poughkeepsie, New York]]. As the head coach from 1973\u201378 and 1980\u201381, Gettleman led his teams to two league titles, competing against schools twice the size as Spackenkill. He spent a season as a volunteer assistant at [[Cal State Long Beach]] in 1979. Gettleman joined the faculty of Kingston High School in 1982 and became the head coach in 1984, leading his team to a Section I Bowl berth. \n\n===Front office===\nHe entered the NFL in 1986 as a scouting intern for the [[Buffalo Bills]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/8829025/carolina-panthers-name-dave-gettleman-general-manager |title=Panthers name Dave Gettleman GM |date=January 10, 2013 |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=April 12, 2013}}</ref> He spent the next seven years working in their scouting department before leaving to accept a scouting job with the [[Denver Broncos]] after the 1993 season. In 1998, he was hired by the [[New York Giants]], who promoted him to Pro Personnel Director the next year. In 2012, he was given the title of Senior Pro Personnel Analyst. \n\nIn January 2013, he was chosen to become the General Manager of the Carolina Panthers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/2013/01/09/3775378/bio-panthers-general-manager-dave.html |title=Bio: Panthers general manager Dave Gettleman |date=January 9, 2013 |publisher=The Charlotte Observer |accessdate=April 12, 2013 }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In the 2015 season, the Panthers reached [[Super Bowl 50]] on February 7, 2016. The Panthers fell to the [[2015 Denver Broncos season|Denver Broncos]] by a score of 24\u201310.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/201602070den.htm|title=Super Bowl 50 - Denver Broncos vs. Carolina Panthers - February 7th, 2016|work=[[Pro-Football-Reference.com]]|accessdate=August 7, 2017}}</ref> On July 17, 2017, the Panthers relieved him of his duties as General Manager.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2722139-dave-gettleman-relieved-of-gm-duties-by-panthers-owner-jerry-richardson |title=Dave Gettleman Relieved of GM Duties by Panthers Owner Jerry Richardson |publisher=Bleacher Report |accessdate=July 17, 2017}}</ref> During Gettleman's tenure as General Manager the Panthers compiled a regular season record of 51-28-1. In that 5-year timeframe the Panthers advanced to the playoffs 4 seasons and won 3 NFC South titles.\n\n===Return to the Giants (2017-present)===\nOn December 28, 2017, Gettleman was named as the new general manager of the New York Giants, returning to the Giants fold after six years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.giants.com/news-and-blogs/article-1/Giants-hire-Dave-Gettleman-as-General-Manager-/f780fe98-f0ec-4cdc-b6fb-4a896a9039e4|title=Giants hire Dave Gettleman as General Manager|access-date=December 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGettleman is a [[Messianic Judaism|Messianic Jew]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://billygraham.org/story/carolina-panthers-general-manager-finds-peace-in-christ/ | title=Carolina Panthers\u2019 General Manager Finds Peace in Christ | publisher=Billy Graham Evangelistic Association | accessdate=4 April 2019}}</ref> On June 5, 2018 it was announced Gettleman would undergo treatment for [[lymphoma]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000935835/article/giants-gm-dave-gettleman-diagnosed-with-lymphoma|title=Giants GM Dave Gettleman diagnosed with lymphoma|website=NFL.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.giants.com/team/staff/dave-gettleman/88ad57b9-fdc9-4d07-8fc0-6fa594e64c6e New York Giants profile]\n\n{{NFL general manager navbox}}\n{{New York Giants}}\n{{Carolina Panthers general manager navbox}}\n{{New York Giants general manager navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gettleman, Dave}}\n[[Category:Carolina Panthers executives]]\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Denver Broncos scouts]]\n[[Category:New York Giants scouts]]\n[[Category:Buffalo Bills scouts]]\n[[Category:New York Giants executives]]\n[[Category:American football offensive tackles]]\n[[Category:Messianic Jews]]\n[[Category:Springfield Pride football players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Boston]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:High school football coaches in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:People from Mattapan]]\n", "name_user": "68.192.8.120"