{"title_page": "Jorge Mier", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jorge Mier\n| image = \n| full_name = Jorge Mier Mart\u00ednez\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1999|2|4|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Oviedo]], Spain\n| height = 1.76m\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]]\n| currentclub = [[Real Oviedo Vetusta|Oviedo B]]\n| clubnumber = \n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Real Oviedo|Oviedo]]\n| years1 = 2016\u2013 | clubs1 = [[Real Oviedo Vetusta|Oviedo B]] | caps1 = 39 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2019\u2013 | clubs2 = [[Real Oviedo|Oviedo]] | caps2 = 1 | goals2 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2015 | nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| club-update = 16 February 2019\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n{{Spanish name|Mier|Mart\u00ednez}}\n\n'''Jorge Mier Mart\u00ednez''' (born 4 February 1999) is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Real Oviedo Vetusta]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Oviedo]], [[Asturias]], Mier was a [[Real Oviedo]] youth graduate. He made his senior debut with [[Real Oviedo Vetusta|the reserves]] on 21 August 2016, starting in a 0\u20130 [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] home draw against [[CD Colunga]].\n\nMier made his first team debut on 3 February 2019, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for goalscorer [[Diego Johannesson|Diegui Johannesson]] in a 2\u20131 home defeat of [[C\u00e1diz CF]] for the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/cronica/2019/02/03/5c571bdf468aeb204d8b4577.html|title=El Oviedo supera al C\u00e1diz, le adelanta y otea la 'zona noble'|trans-title=Oviedo overcome C\u00e1diz, take advantage of them and scan the 'noble zone'|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=3 February 2019|accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nMier's [[twin]] brother [[Javier Mier Mart\u00ednez|Javi]] is also a footballer who plays as a [[midfielder]]. Their older brother, [[Alberto Mier Mart\u00ednez|Tato]], was also an Oviedo youth graduate.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lavozdeasturias.es/noticia/azulcarbayon/2018/04/17/sangre-azul/00031523987400836834475.htm|title=Sangre azul|trans-title=Blue blood|publisher=La Voz de Asturias|language=es|date=17 April 2018|accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|21776}}\n*{{LaPreferente|176759<!-- /jorge-mier -->}}\n*{{Soccerway|jorge-mier-martinez/427906}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mier, Jorge}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Twin sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Twin people from Spain]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Oviedo]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Asturian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Real Oviedo Vetusta players]]\n[[Category:Real Oviedo players]]\n[[Category:Spain youth international footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jorge Mier\n| image =\n| fullname = Jorge Mier Mart\u00ednez\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1999|2|4|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Oviedo]], Spain\n| height = 1.76m\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]]\n| currentclub = [[Real Oviedo Vetusta|Oviedo B]]\n| clubnumber = \n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Real Oviedo|Oviedo]]\n| years1 = 2016\u2013 | clubs1 = [[Real Oviedo Vetusta|Oviedo B]] | caps1 = 39 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2019\u2013 | clubs2 = [[Real Oviedo|Oviedo]] | caps2 = 1 | goals2 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2015 | nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 \n| club-update = 16 February 2019\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n{{spanish name|Mier|Mart\u00ednez}}\n'''Jorge Mier Mart\u00ednez''' (born 4 February 1999) is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Real Oviedo Vetusta]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Oviedo]], [[Asturias]], Mier was a [[Real Oviedo]] youth graduate. He made his senior debut with [[Real Oviedo Vetusta|the reserves]] on 21 August 2016, starting in a 0\u20130 [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] home draw against [[CD Colunga]].\n\nMier made his first team debut on 3 February 2019, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for goalscorer [[Diego Johannesson|Diegui Johannesson]] in a 2\u20131 home defeat of [[C\u00e1diz CF]] for the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/cronica/2019/02/03/5c571bdf468aeb204d8b4577.html|title=El Oviedo supera al C\u00e1diz, le adelanta y otea la 'zona noble'|trans-title=Oviedo overcome C\u00e1diz, take advantage of them and scan the 'noble zone'|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=3 February 2019|accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nMier's [[twin]] brother [[Javier Mier Mart\u00ednez|Javi]] is also a footballer who plays as a [[midfielder]]. Their older brother, [[Alberto Mier Mart\u00ednez|Tato]], was also an Oviedo youth graduate.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lavozdeasturias.es/noticia/azulcarbayon/2018/04/17/sangre-azul/00031523987400836834475.htm|title=Sangre azul|trans-title=Blue blood|publisher=La Voz de Asturias|language=es|date=17 April 2018|accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|21776|Jorge Mier}}\n*{{LaPreferente|176759/jorge-mier|Jorge Mier}}\n*{{Soccerway|jorge-mier-martinez/427906|Jorge Mier}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mier, Jorge}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]