{"title_page": "Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen", "text_new": "The '''Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen''' is a member of the [[Helmholtz Association of German Research Centres]]. It was founded in 1964 as \"Society for Radiation\" (Gesellschaft f\u00fcr Strahlenforschung - GSF) and is a joint venture by the [[Federal Ministry of Education and Research (Germany)|Federal Ministry of Education and Research]] and [https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayerisches_Staatsministerium_f%C3%BCr_Wirtschaft,_Landesentwicklung_und_Energie Bavarian State Ministry of Finance and Home]. \n\n'''Mission'''<br>\n\nThe mission of Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen is to find new personalized medical solutions for the prevention, diagnosis and therapy of environmentally triggered diseases to promote a healthier society in a rapidly changing world.\n\n'''Management'''<br>\n\n[[Matthias Tsch\u00f6p|Prof. Dr. H. Matthias Tsch\u00f6p]] has been the Scientific Director and Chief Executive Officer of the Center since 2018.\nIn 2019 [[Kerstin G\u00fcnther]] joined the Center and is now the Commercial and Technical Director of Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen.\n\n'''[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/about-us/locations/index.html Campus]'''<br>\n\nThe main campus is located in Neuherberg, a district of Oberschlei\u00dfheim, right outside of [[Munich]]\u2019s city borders. The campus has a size of 52.3 hectares. In addition, the Center maintains research facilities inside the city area of Munich, Augsburg, T\u00fcbingen, Hanover, Dresden and Leipzig.\n\n'''Legal form'''<br>\n\nHelmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen is a limited liability company according to German law and is financed by a ratio of 90:10 by its two shareholders, the Federal Government and the Free State of Bavaria.\n\n'''[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/helmholtz-zentrum-muenchen/index.html Research Focus]'''<br>\n \nThe Center focuses its research on five key areas:\n\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/metabolic-health/index.html Metabolic Health]\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/environmental-health/index.html Environmental Health] \n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/molecular-targets-therapies/index.html Molecular Targets and Therapies] \n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/cellprogramming-repair/index.html Cell Programming and Repair] \n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/bioengineering-digital-health/index.html Bioengineering and Digital Health]\n\n'''[https://www.pioneercampus.org/ The Helmholtz Pioneer Campus] (HPC)'''<br>\n\nThe HPC is an innovation campus where young investigators research for novel solutions in the fields of biomedical sciences, engineering and digitization in the research environment of Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen.\n\n'''[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/innovationen/translational-and-clinical-projects/translational-research-centers/index.html Translational and Clinical Projects]'''<br>\n\nTranslational research approaches at the Center are developed in cooperation with clinical partners within a dynamic project portfolio: \n\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/idf/index.html Diabetes Study Center]\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/ilbd/index.html Comprehensive Pneumology Center]\n* [https://www.zaum-online.de/ Center of Allergy and Environment]\n\n'''[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/career/graduates-entry-level-professionals/research/index.html Career development]'''<br>\n\nThe Center has one Helmholtz Graduate School (HELENA) in cooperation with the Ludwig Maximilian University Munich (LMU) and the Technical University Munich (TUM), and five Helmholtz Research Schools. The schools offer doctoral students in-depth research in the fields of diabetes, lung and radiation research, epigenetics and data science:\n\n* [https://www.helmholtz-helena.de/ Helmholtz Graduate School Environmental Health (HELENA)]\n* [https://www.helmholtzresearchschool-diabetes.org/ International Helmholtz Research School for Diabetes]\n* [https://www.helmholtzresearchschool-epigenetics.org/ Helmholtz International Epigenetics Research School]\n* [https://www.cpc-researchschool.org/ CPC-Research School Lung Biology and Disease]\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/helmholtz-research-school-of-radiation-sciences-rs2/index.html Helmholtz Research School of Radiation Science]\n* [https://www.mu-ds.de/ Munich School for Data Science]\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/index.html Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen]\n* [http://www.helmholtz-helena.de Helmholtz Graduate School Environmental Health ]\n* [http://www.helmholtz.de/en/ Helmholtz Association]\n* [http://www.cpc-munich.org/ Comprehensive Pneumology Center]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{coord|48|13|21|N|11|35|36|E|region:DE-BY_type:landmark_source:kolossus-dewiki|display=title}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Helmholtz Zentrum Munchen}}\n[[Category:Medical research institutes in Germany]]\n[[Category:Medical and health organisations based in Bavaria]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen''' is a member of the [[Helmholtz Association of German Research Centres]]. It was founded in 1964 as \"Society for Radiation\" (Gesellschaft f\u00fcr Strahlenforschung - GSF) and is a joint venture by the [[Federal Ministry of Education and Research (Germany)|Federal Ministry of Education and Research]] and [https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayerisches_Staatsministerium_f%C3%BCr_Wirtschaft,_Landesentwicklung_und_Energie Bavarian State Ministry of Finance and Home]. \n\n'''Mission'''<br>\n\nThe mission of Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen is to find new personalized medical solutions for the prevention, diagnosis and therapy of environmentally triggered diseases to promote a healthier society in a rapidly changing world.\n\n'''Management'''<br>\n\n[[Matthias Tsch\u00f6p|Prof. Dr. H. Matthias Tsch\u00f6p]] has been the Scientific Director and Chief Executive Officer of the Center since 2018.\nIn 2019 [[Kerstin G\u00fcnther]] joined the Center and is now the Commercial and Technical Director of Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen.\n\n'''[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/about-us/locations/index.html Campus]'''<br>\n\nThe main campus is located in Neuherberg, a district of Oberschlei\u00dfheim, right outside of [[Munich]]\u2019s city borders. The campus has a size of 52.3 hectares. In addition, the Center maintains research facilities inside the city area of Munich, Augsburg, T\u00fcbingen, Hanover, Dresden and Leipzig.\n\n'''Legal form'''<br>\n\nHelmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen is a limited liability company according to German law and is financed by a ratio of 90:10 by its two shareholders, the Federal Government and the Free State of Bavaria.\n\n'''[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/helmholtz-zentrum-muenchen/index.html Research Focus]'''<br>\n \nThe Center focuses its research on five key areas:\n\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/metabolic-health/index.html Metabolic Health]\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/environmental-health/index.html Environmental Health] \n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/molecular-targets-therapies/index.html Molecular Targets and Therapies] \n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/cellprogramming-repair/index.html Cell Programming and Repair] \n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/research/research-institutions/bioengineering-digital-health/index.html Bioengineering and Digital Health]\n\n'''[https://www.pioneercampus.org/ The Helmholtz Pioneer Campus] (HPC)'''<br>\n\nThe HPC is an innovation campus where young investigators research for novel solutions in the fields of biomedical sciences, engineering and digitization in the research environment of Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen.\n\n'''[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/innovationen/translational-and-clinical-projects/translational-research-centers/index.html Translational and Clinical Projects]'''<br>\n\nTranslational research approaches at the Center are developed in cooperation with clinical partners within a dynamic project portfolio. \n\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/idf/index.html Diabetes Study Center]\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/ilbd/index.html Comprehensive Pneumology Center]\n* [https://www.zaum-online.de/ Center of Allergy and Environment]\n\n'''[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/career/graduates-entry-level-professionals/research/index.html Career development]'''<br>\n\nOne Helmholtz Graduate School (HELENA) in cooperation with the Ludwig Maximilian University Munich (LMU) and the Technical University Munich (TUM) and five Helmholtz Research Schools offer doctoral students in-depth research in the fields of diabetes, lung and radiation research, epigenetics and data science:\n\n* [https://www.helmholtz-helena.de/ Helmholtz Graduate School Environmental Health (HELENA)]\n* [https://www.helmholtzresearchschool-diabetes.org/ International Helmholtz Research School for Diabetes]\n* [https://www.helmholtzresearchschool-epigenetics.org/ Helmholtz International Epigenetics Research School]\n* [https://www.cpc-researchschool.org/ CPC-Research School Lung Biology and Disease]\n* [https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/helmholtz-research-school-of-radiation-sciences-rs2/index.html Helmholtz Research School of Radiation Science]\n* [https://www.mu-ds.de/ Munich School for Data Science]\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/en/index.html Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen]\n* [http://www.helmholtz-helena.de Helmholtz Graduate School Environmental Health ]\n* [http://www.helmholtz.de/en/ Helmholtz Association]\n* [http://www.cpc-munich.org/ Comprehensive Pneumology Center]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{coord|48|13|21|N|11|35|36|E|region:DE-BY_type:landmark_source:kolossus-dewiki|display=title}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Helmholtz Zentrum Munchen}}\n[[Category:Medical research institutes in Germany]]\n[[Category:Medical and health organisations based in Bavaria]]\n", "name_user": "Ako helmholtz", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helmholtz_Zentrum_M%C3%BCnchen"}
{"title_page": "Carlos Parra Aranzo", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Spanish name|Parra|Aranzo}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Carlos Parra\n| image = \n| caption = \n| full_name = Carlos Parra Aranzo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|2|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Madrid]], Spain\n| height = 1.70 m\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]]\n| currentclub = [[Zamora CF|Zamora]]\n| clubnumber = 2\n| youthyears1 = 2007\u20132014 | youthclubs1 = [[Real Madrid C.F. (youth)|Real Madrid]]\n| youthyears2 = 2014\u20132015 | youthclubs2 = [[CF Rayo Majadahonda|Rayo Majadahonda]]\n| youthyears3 = 2015 | youthclubs3 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n| years1 = 2015 | clubs1 = [[CF Rayo Majadahonda|Rayo Majadahonda]] | caps1 = 1 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs2 = [[CD Toledo B|Toledo B]] | caps2 = 26 | goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs3 = [[F\u00fatbol Alcobendas Sport|Alcobendas]] | caps3 = 18 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2017\u20132019 | clubs4 = [[AD Alcorc\u00f3n B|Alcorc\u00f3n B]] | caps4 = 57 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2019 | clubs5 = [[AD Alcorc\u00f3n|Alcorc\u00f3n]] | caps5 = 1 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2019\u2013 | clubs6 = [[Zamora CF|Zamora]] | caps6 = 25 | goals6 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update = 00:28, 10 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n'''Carlos Parra Aranzo''' (born 18 February 1996) is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Zamora CF]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Madrid]], Parra represented [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]'s [[Real Madrid C.F. (youth)|youth setup]] for seven years before joining [[CF Rayo Majadahonda]] in 2014. Initially assigned to the ''Juvenil'' squad, he made his first team debut on 25 January 2015, starting in a 6\u20132 [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] home routing of [[Alcobendas CF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elgoldemadriz.com/rayo-majadahonda-6-2-alcobendas-levitt-borja-acha-y-portilla-elevan-al-rayo/|title=RAYO MAJADAHONDA 6\u20132 ALCOBENDAS LEVITT {{!}} Borja Acha y Portilla elevan al Rayo|trans-title=RAYO MAJADAHONDA 6\u20132 ALCOBENDAS LEVITT {{!}} Borja Acha and Portilla raise up Rayo|publisher=El Gol de Madriz|language=es|date=25 January 2015|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nFor the [[2015\u201316 Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|2015\u201316 campaign]], Parra joined [[CD Toledo]]'s [[CD Toledo B|reserves]], after a short stint at [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]. On 23 July 2016, he moved to [[F\u00fatbol Alcobendas Sport]] also in the fourth division.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elgoldemadriz.com/fichajes-mas-refuerzos-para-los-dos-alcobendas/|title=FICHAJES {{!}} M\u00e1s refuerzos para los dos Alcobendas|trans-title=SIGNINGS {{!}} More additions for the two Alcobendas|publisher=El Gol de Madriz|language=es|date=23 July 2016|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 July 2017, Parra agreed to a contract with [[AD Alcorc\u00f3n]], being initially assigned to [[AD Alcorc\u00f3n|B-team]] also in the fourth tier.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adalcorcon.com/noticia/el-lateral-derecho-parra-novena-incorporacion|title=El lateral derecho Parra, novena incorporaci\u00f3n|trans-title=Right back Parra, ninth addition|publisher=AD Alcorc\u00f3n|language=es|date=12 July 2017|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> He made his professional debut on 16 February 2019, coming on as a first-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for injured [[David Gonz\u00e1lez Plata|Nono]] in a 0\u20131 loss at [[Real Oviedo]] for the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/cronica/2019/02/16/5c686b06268e3e495a8b4589.html|title=Tejera muestra el camino a un Oviedo lanzado|trans-title=Tejera shows the way to an in-form Oviedo|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=16 February 2019|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 July 2019, Parra signed for [[Zamora CF]] also in the fourth division.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.zamoracf.es/el-zamora-cf-ficha-al-lateral-madrileno-carlos-parra/|title=El Zamora CF ficha al lateral madrile\u00f1o Carlos Parra|trans-title=Zamora CF sign Madrilenian full back Carlos Parra|publisher=Zamora CF|language=es|date=12 July 2019|accessdate=30 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.realmadrid.com/cs/Satellite?c=RM_Jugador_FA&cid=1330037243736&pagename=RealMadridResponsive%2FRM_Jugador_FA%2FRM_Jugador Real Madrid profile]\n*[https://www.adalcorcon.com/jugador/parra AD Alcorc\u00f3n profile] {{in lang|es}}\n*{{BDFutbol|20675|Carlos Parra}}\n*{{LaPreferente|153876<!-- /parra -->|Carlos Parra}}\n*{{Soccerway|carlos-parra-aranzo/564927|Carlos Parra}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Parra Aranzo, Carlos}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Madrid]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Madrilenian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:CF Rayo Majadahonda players]]\n[[Category:AD Alcorc\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:AD Alcorc\u00f3n footballers]]\n[[Category:Zamora CF footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{spanish name|Parra|Aranzo}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Carlos Parra\n| image = \n| caption =\n| fullname = Carlos Parra Aranzo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|2|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Madrid]], Spain\n| height = 1.70 m\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]]\n| currentclub = [[Zamora CF|Zamora]]\n| clubnumber = 2\n| youthyears1 = 2007\u20132014 | youthclubs1 = [[Real Madrid C.F. (youth)|Real Madrid]]\n| youthyears2 = 2014\u20132015 | youthclubs2 = [[CF Rayo Majadahonda|Rayo Majadahonda]]\n| youthyears3 = 2015 | youth