{"title_page": "Juan Pablo Vojvoda", "text_new": "{{Spanish name|Vojvoda|Rizzo}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Juan Pablo Vojvoda\n| image = Universidad de Chile v Uni\u00f3n La Calera 20200227 16.jpg\n| full_name = Juan Pablo Vojvoda Rizzo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1975|5|13|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[General Baldissera]], Argentina\n| height = 1.85m\n| currentclub = [[Uni\u00f3n La Calera]] (Manager)\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Cruz Alta\n| youthyears2 = 1989\u20131995 | youthclubs2 = [[Newell's Old Boys]]\n| years1 = 1995\u20132002 | clubs1 = [[Newell's Old Boys]] | caps1 = 126 | goals1 = 4\n| years2 = 2002\u20132003 | clubs2 = [[SD Compostela|Compostela]] | caps2 = 28 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2003\u20132005 | clubs3 = [[Algeciras CF|Algeciras]] | caps3 = 55 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2005\u20132006 | clubs4 = [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]] | caps4 = 32 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2006\u20132009 | clubs5 = [[CD Baza|Baza]] | caps5 = 106 | goals5 = 11\n| years6 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs6 = [[Tiro Federal]] | caps6 = 34 | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2010\u20132012 | clubs7 = [[Sportivo Belgrano]] | caps7 = 80 | goals7 = 1\n| years8 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs8 = Sarmiento de Leones | caps8 = 24 | goals8 = 1\n| totalcaps = 485 | totalgoals = 17\n| manageryears1 = 2013\u20132017 | managerclubs1 = [[Newell's Old Boys]] (youth)\n| manageryears2 = 2016 | managerclubs2 = [[Newell's Old Boys]] (caretaker)\n| manageryears3 = 2017 | managerclubs3 = [[Newell's Old Boys]] (caretaker)\n| manageryears4 = 2017\u20132018 | managerclubs4 = [[Defensa y Justicia]]\n| manageryears5 = 2018\u20132019 | managerclubs5 = [[Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba|Talleres]]\n| manageryears6 = 2019  | managerclubs6 = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Hurac\u00e1n|Hurac\u00e1n]]\n| manageryears7 = 2020\u2013 | managerclubs7 = [[Uni\u00f3n La Calera]]\n}}\n\n'''Juan Pablo Vojvoda Rizzo''' (born 13 May 1975) is an Argentine retired [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]], and is the [[Coach (sport)|manager]] of [[Uni\u00f3n La Calera]].\n\n==Playing career==\nBorn in [[General Baldissera]] but raised in Cruz Alta, Vojvoda joined [[Newell's Old Boys]]' youth setup at the age of 14.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/2137382-la-historia-de-juan-pablo-vojvoda-la-pasion-por-la-pelota-y-la-graduacion-que-espera-en-la-universidad|title=La historia de Juan Pablo Vojvoda: la pasi\u00f3n por la pelota y la graduaci\u00f3n que espera en la Universidad|trans-title=The story of Juan Pablo Vojvoda: the passion for the ball and  the graduation which awaits him at the university|publisher=[[La Naci\u00f3n]]|language=es|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> He made his senior debut with the main squad in 1995, and went on to feature regularly in the following seven seasons, never establishing himself as a regular starter.\n\nIn 2002 Vojvoda moved abroad, after signing for [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] side [[SD Compostela]] on loan for one year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eldia.es/jornada/2002-07-30/7-BREVES.htm|title=Un argentino al Compostela|trans-title=An Argentine at Compostela|publisher=El D\u00eda|language=es|date=30 July 2002|accessdate=20 February 2019}}</ref> He stayed in the country for the following six seasons, representing [[Algeciras CF]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.diariodeleon.es/noticias/deportes/algeciras-sera-destino-real-vojvoda-deja-compostela_89921.html|title=Algeciras ser\u00e1 el destino real de Vojvoda, que deja el Compostela|trans-title=Algeciras will be the destiny of Vojvoda, who leaves Compostela|publisher=Diario de Le\u00f3n|language=es|date=9 July 2003|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.es/hemeroteca/historico-05-07-2005/abc/CastillaLeon/tome-satisfecho-con-las-llegadas-de-vojvoda-y-javicho-a-la-cultural_203588059728.html|title=Tom\u00e9, satisfecho con las llegadas de Vojvoda y Javicho a la Cultural|trans-title=Tom\u00e9, satisfied with the arrivals of Vojvoda and Javicho to Cultural|publisher=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]|language=es|date=5 July 2005|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> and [[CD Baza]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diariodeleon.es/noticias/vojvoda-rescinde-vinculacion-cultural-jugara-baza_271465.html|title=Vojvoda rescinde su vinculaci\u00f3n con la Cultural y jugar\u00e1 en el Baza|trans-title=Vojvoda rescinds his link with Cultural and will play at Baza|publisher=Diario de Le\u00f3n|language=es|date=21 July 2006|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nVojvoda returned to his home country on 15 July 2009, joining [[Tiro Federal]] of the [[Primera B Nacional]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lacapital.com.ar/vojvoda-es-casi-un-tigre-maacutes-n672997|title=Vojvoda es casi un Tigre m\u00e1s|trans-title=Vojvoda is nearly another ''Tigre''|publisher=[[La Capital]]|language=es|date=15 July 2009|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> He subsequently played for [[Sportivo Belgrano]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.diariosports.com.ar/noticia/futbol/16/06/2010/vojvoda-es-de-sportivo|title=Vojvoda es de Sportivo|trans-title=Vojvoda is of Sportivo|publisher=Diariosports|language=es|date=16 June 2010|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> and Sarmiento de Leones,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascensodelinterior.com.ar/noticias/425/refuerzos-en-el-demonio|title=Refuerzo de lujo, Juan Pablo Vojvoda|trans-title=Luxury addition, Juan Pablo Vojvoda|publisher=Ascenso del Interior|language=es|date=28 July 2012|accessdate=20 February 2019}}</ref> retiring with the latter in 2013 at the age of 38.\n\n==Managerial career==\nShortly after retiring Vojvoda took up coaching, being in charge of the youth categories of his first club Newell's. On 10 July 2015, he was named manager of the club's reserve side.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newellsoldboys.com.ar/page/noticias_futbol/id/970/title/Organigrama-del-Departamento-de-F%C3%BAtbol|title=Organigrama del Departamento de F\u00fatbol|trans-title=Football Department's Organization Chart|publisher=Newell's Old Boys|language=es|date=10 July 2015|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> He was also an interim manager of the first team for two occasions: in 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telam.com.ar/notas/201602/136346-juan-pablo-vojvoda-futbol-newells-rosario-central-scoponi-osella.html|title=Juan Pablo Vojvoda, entrenador interino de Newell's|trans-title=Juan Pablo Vojvoda, interim manager of Newell's|publisher=[[T\u00e9lam]]|language=es|date=16 February 2016|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> and in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://argentina.as.com/argentina/2017/06/05/futbol/1496628087_440344.html|title=Vojvoda asumir\u00e1 el martes como interino en Newell's|trans-title=Vojvoda will take over on Tuesday as interim at Newell's|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=5 June 2017|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 October 2017, Vojvoda was named manager of [[Defensa y Justicia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tycsports.com/futbol/defensa-oficializo-la-llegada-de-vojvoda-su-nuevo-dt.html|title=Defensa oficializ\u00f3 la llegada de Vojvoda, su nuevo DT|trans-title=Defensa made official the arrival of Vojvoda, their new manager|publisher=TyC Sports|language=es|date=7 October 2017|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> The following 28 May, he was named at the helm of [[Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lacapital.com.ar/ovacion/vojvoda-fue-oficializado-como-nuevo-dt-talleres-cordoba-n1614790.html|title=Vojvoda fue oficializado como nuevo DT de Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba|trans-title=Vojvoda was officially appointed new manager of Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba|publisher=La Capital|language=es|date=28 May 2018|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt the end of May 2019, Vojvoda was appointed manager of [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Hurac\u00e1n]] for the 2019/20 season.<ref>[https://cahuracan.com/2019/06/03/se-presento-juan-pablo-vojvoda-en-el-palacio/ Se present\u00f3 Juan Pablo Vojvoda en el Palacio], cahuracan.com, 3 June 2019</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn in Argentina, Vojvoda is of Croatian and Italian descent, and holds an Italian passport.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mundod.lavoz.com.ar/futbol/como-se-pronuncia-vojvoda-la-explicacion-del-propio-dt-de-talleres|title=\u00bfC\u00f3mo se pronuncia Vojvoda? La explicaci\u00f3n del propio DT de Talleres|website=Mundo D}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/futbolgallego/2002/09/02/0003_1214468.htm|title=El portero Tito fich\u00f3 por el Compos al l\u00edmite del plazo|date=September 2, 2002|website=La Voz de Galicia}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|4702}}\n*{{BDFA|411}}\n*{{LaPreferente|10713<!-- /vojvoda -->}}\n*{{Soccerway coach|juan-vojvoda/90967}}\n*{{FootballDatabase.eu|131112<!-- -juan_pablo-vojvoda -->}}\n\n{{Uni\u00f3n La Calera squad}}\n{{Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n managers}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Juan Pablo Vojvoda managerial positions\n|list1=\n{{Newell's Old Boys managers}}\n{{Defensa y Justicia managers}}\n{{Hurac\u00e1n managers}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vojvoda, Juan Pablo}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Argentine footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine football managers]]\n[[Category:Argentine people of Croatian descent]]\n[[Category:Argentine people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Primera B Nacional players]]\n[[Category:Newell's Old Boys footballers]]\n[[Category:Tiro Federal footballers]]\n[[Category:Sportivo Belgrano footballers]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:SD Compostela footballers]]\n[[Category:Algeciras CF footballers]]\n[[Category:Cultural Leonesa footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n managers]]\n[[Category:Newell's Old Boys managers]]\n[[Category:Defensa y Justicia managers]]\n[[Category:Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba managers]]\n[[Category:Club Atl\u00e9tico Hurac\u00e1n managers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Chile]]\n[[Category:Uni\u00f3n La Calera managers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Spanish name|Vojvoda|Rizzo}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Juan Pablo Vojvoda\n| image = Universidad de Chile v Uni\u00f3n La Calera 20200227 16.jpg\n| fullname = Juan Pablo Vojvoda Rizzo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1975|5|13|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[General Baldissera]], Argentina\n| height = 1.85m\n| currentclub = [[Uni\u00f3n La Calera]] (Manager)\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Cruz Alta\n| youthyears2 = 1989\u20131995 | youthclubs2 = [[Newell's Old Boys]]\n| years1 = 1995\u20132002 | clubs1 = [[Newell's Old Boys]] | caps1 = 126 | goals1 = 4\n| years2 = 2002\u20132003 | clubs2 = [[SD Compostela|Compostela]] | caps2 = 28 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2003\u20132005 | clubs3 = [[Algeciras CF|Algeciras]] | caps3 = 55 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2005\u20132006 | clubs4 = [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]] | caps4 = 32 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2006\u20132009 | clubs5 = [[CD Baza|Baza]] | caps5 = 106 | goals5 = 11\n| years6 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs6 = [[Tiro Federal]] | caps6 = 34 | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2010\u20132012 | clubs7 = [[Sportivo Belgrano]] | caps7 = 80 | goals7 = 1\n| years8 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs8 = Sarmiento de Leones | caps8 = 24 | goals8 = 1\n| totalcaps = 485 | totalgoals = 17\n| manageryears1 = 2013\u20132017 | managerclubs1 = [[Newell's Old Boys]] (youth)\n| manageryears2 = 2016 | managerclubs2 = [[Newell's Old Boys]] (caretaker)\n| manageryears3 = 2017 | managerclubs3 = [[Newell's Old Boys]] (caretaker)\n| manageryears4 = 2017\u20132018 | managerclubs4 = [[Defensa y Justicia]]\n| manageryears5 = 2018\u20132019 | managerclubs5 = [[Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba|Talleres]]\n| manageryears6 = 2019  | managerclubs6 = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Hurac\u00e1n|Hurac\u00e1n]]\n| manageryears7 = 2020\u2013 | managerclubs7 = [[Uni\u00f3n La Calera]]\n}}\n\n'''Juan Pablo Vojvoda Rizzo''' (born 13 May 1975) is an Argentine retired [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]], and is the [[Coach (sport)|manager]] of [[Uni\u00f3n La Calera]].\n\n==Playing career==\nBorn in [[General Baldissera]] but raised in Cruz Alta, Vojvoda joined [[Newell's Old Boys]]' youth setup at the age of 14.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/2137382-la-historia-de-juan-pablo-vojvoda-la-pasion-por-la-pelota-y-la-graduacion-que-espera-en-la-universidad|title=La historia de Juan Pablo Vojvoda: la pasi\u00f3n por la pelota y la graduaci\u00f3n que espera en la Universidad|trans-title=The story of Juan Pablo Vojvoda: the passion for the ball and  the graduation which awaits him at the university|publisher=[[La Naci\u00f3n]]|language=es|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> He made his senior debut with the main squad in 1995, and went on to feature regularly in the following seven seasons, never establishing himself as a regular starter.\n\nIn 2002 Vojvoda moved abroad, after signing for [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] side [[SD Compostela]] on loan for one year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eldia.es/jornada/2002-07-30/7-BREVES.htm|title=Un argentino al Compostela|trans-title=An Argentine at Compostela|publisher=El D\u00eda|language=es|date=30 July 2002|accessdate=20 February 2019}}</ref> He stayed in the country for the following six seasons, representing [[Algeciras CF]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.diariodeleon.es/noticias/deportes/algeciras-sera-destino-real-vojvoda-deja-compostela_89921.html|title=Algeciras ser\u00e1 el destino real de Vojvoda, que deja el Compostela|trans-title=Algeciras will be the destiny of Vojvoda, who leaves Compostela|publisher=Diario de Le\u00f3n|language=es|date=9 July 2003|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.es/hemeroteca/historico-05-07-2005/abc/CastillaLeon/tome-satisfecho-con-las-llegadas-de-vojvoda-y-javicho-a-la-cultural_203588059728.html|title=Tom\u00e9, satisfecho con las llegadas de Vojvoda y Javicho a la Cultural|trans-title=Tom\u00e9, satisfied with the arrivals of Vojvoda and Javicho to Cultural|publisher=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]|language=es|date=5 July 2005|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> and [[CD Baza]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diariodeleon.es/noticias/vojvoda-rescinde-vinculacion-cultural-jugara-baza_271465.html|title=Vojvoda rescinde su vinculaci\u00f3n con la Cultural y jugar\u00e1 en el Baza|trans-title=Vojvoda rescinds his link with Cultural and will play at Baza|publisher=Diario de Le\u00f3n|language=es|date=21 July 2006|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nVojvoda returned to his home country on 15 July 2009, joining [[Tiro Federal]] of the [[Primera B Nacional]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lacapital.com.ar/vojvoda-es-casi-un-tigre-maacutes-n672997|title=Vojvoda es casi un Tigre m\u00e1s|trans-title=Vojvoda is nearly another ''Tigre''|publisher=[[La Capital]]|language=es|date=15 July 2009|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> He subsequently played for [[Sportivo Belgrano]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.diariosports.com.ar/noticia/futbol/16/06/2010/vojvoda-es-de-sportivo|title=Vojvoda es de Sportivo|trans-title=Vojvoda is of Sportivo|publisher=Diariosports|language=es|date=16 June 2010|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> and Sarmiento de Leones,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascensodelinterior.com.ar/noticias/425/refuerzos-en-el-demonio|title=Refuerzo de lujo, Juan Pablo Vojvoda|trans-title=Luxury addition, Juan Pablo Vojvoda|publisher=Ascenso del Interior|language=es|date=28 July 2012|accessdate=20 February 2019}}</ref> retiring with the latter in 2013 at the age of 38.\n\n==Managerial career==\nShortly after retiring Vojvoda took up coaching, being in charge of the youth categories of his first club Newell's. On 10 July 2015, he was named manager of the club's reserve side.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newellsoldboys.com.ar/page/noticias_futbol/id/970/title/Organigrama-del-Departamento-de-F%C3%BAtbol|title=Organigrama del Departamento de F\u00fatbol|trans-title=Football Department's Organization Chart|publisher=Newell's Old Boys|language=es|date=10 July 2015|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> He was also an interim manager of the first team for two occasions: in 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telam.com.ar/notas/201602/136346-juan-pablo-vojvoda-futbol-newells-rosario-central-scoponi-osella.html|title=Juan Pablo Vojvoda, entrenador interino de Newell's|trans-title=Juan Pablo Vojvoda, interim manager of Newell's|publisher=[[T\u00e9lam]]|language=es|date=16 February 2016|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> and in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://argentina.as.com/argentina/2017/06/05/futbol/1496628087_440344.html|title=Vojvoda asumir\u00e1 el martes como interino en Newell's|trans-title=Vojvoda will take over on Tuesday as interim at Newell's|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=5 June 2017|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 October 2017, Vojvoda was named manager of [[Defensa y Justicia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tycsports.com/futbol/defensa-oficializo-la-llegada-de-vojvoda-su-nuevo-dt.html|title=Defensa oficializ\u00f3 la llegada de Vojvoda, su nuevo DT|trans-title=Defensa made official the arrival of Vojvoda, their new manager|publisher=TyC Sports|language=es|date=7 October 2017|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> The following 28 May, he was named at the helm of [[Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lacapital.com.ar/ovacion/vojvoda-fue-oficializado-como-nuevo-dt-talleres-cordoba-n1614790.html|title=Vojvoda fue oficializado como nuevo DT de Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba|trans-title=Vojvoda was officially appointed new manager of Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba|publisher=La Capital|language=es|date=28 May 2018|accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt the end of May 2019, Vojvoda was appointed manager of [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Hurac\u00e1n]] for the 2019/20 season.<ref>[https://cahuracan.com/2019/06/03/se-presento-juan-pablo-vojvoda-en-el-palacio/ Se present\u00f3 Juan Pablo Vojvoda en el Palacio], cahuracan.com, 3 June 2019</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn in Argentina, Vojvoda is of Croatian and Italian descent, and holds an Italian passport.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mundod.lavoz.com.ar/futbol/como-se-pronuncia-vojvoda-la-explicacion-del-propio-dt-de-talleres|title=\u00bfC\u00f3mo se pronuncia Vojvoda? La explicaci\u00f3n del propio DT de Talleres|website=Mundo D}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/futbolgallego/2002/09/02/0003_1214468.htm|title=El portero Tito fich\u00f3 por el Compos al l\u00edmite del plazo|date=September 2, 2002|website=La Voz de Galicia}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|4702}}\n*{{BDFA|id=411}}\n*{{LaPreferente|10713/vojvoda}}\n*{{Soccerway coach|juan-vojvoda/90967}}\n*[https://www.footballdatabase.eu/en/player/details/131112-juan_pablo-vojvoda Juan Pablo Vojvoda] at Footballdatabase\n\n{{Uni\u00f3n La Calera squad}}\n{{Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n managers}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Juan Pablo Vojvoda managerial positions\n|list1=\n{{Newell's Old Boys managers}}\n{{Defensa y Justicia managers}}\n{{Hurac\u00e1n managers}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vojvoda, Juan Pablo}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Argentine footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine football managers]]\n[[Category:Argentine people of Croatian descent]]\n[[Category:Argentine people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Primera B Nacional players]]\