NA]]\n|[[GPS]]/[[GLONASS]]\n|[[Near Field Communication|NFC]]\n|Bluetooth 4.0 BLE||\n|Water Resistant\n|IR Remote\n|[[Universal Serial Bus|USB 2.0]] (Micro-B port, USB charging)\n|[[USB On-The-Go|USB OTG]]\n|{{convert|3.50|mm|in|abbr=on}} [[Phone connector (audio)|headphone jack]]\n}}\n| other         = \n| sar           = \n* SAR US (1 g): <br /> \t0.63 W/kg (head) <br />   0.82 W/kg (body)  \n* SAR EU (10 g):  <br />\t0.97 W/kg (head)  <br />    0.56 W/kg (body) \n<ref> http://www.gsmarena.com/samsung_galaxy_s5_mini-6252.php </ref>\n| hac           = \n| website       = \n| references    = \n}}\n\nThe '''Samsung Galaxy S5 Mini''' is an [[Android (operating system)|Android]] [[smartphone]] developed by [[Samsung Electronics]]. It was announced in May 2014 and released on July 1, 2014. The S5 Mini is a mid-range model of its flagship [[Samsung Galaxy S5|Galaxy S5]] smartphone and a successor to the [[Samsung Galaxy S4 Mini|Galaxy S4 Mini]]. It competes with the [[HTC One Mini 2]] and the [[Sony Xperia Z1 Compact]]. It has a similar design and software features to its high-end counterpart, the Galaxy S5.<ref name=\"gsmarena\">[http://www.gsmarena.com/samsung_galaxy_s5_mini-6252.php Samsung Galaxy S5 Mini], GSMArena.com</ref><ref name=Announced>[http://tech.firstpost.com/news%20-%20analysis/samsung-unveils-watered-down-galaxy-s5-mini-but-its-missing-s5s-best-feature-226737.html Samsung unveils watered-down Galaxy S5 Mini, but it\u2019s missing S5\u2032s best feature], firstpost.com</ref>\n\n==Specifications==\nThe S5 Mini uses an almost identical variant of the S5's polycarbonate perforated faux-leather hardware design. Internally, it features a quad-core 1.4&nbsp;GHz [[Exynos (system on chip)|Exynos 3 Quad 3470]] (for the SM-G800F) or an equally-clocked [[Qualcomm Snapdragon]] 400 MSM8228 (for SM-800A and SM-G800H<ref name=\"sm-g800h\">{{cite web | url=http://www.devicespecifications.com/en/model/2f592f7d | title=Samsung Galaxy S5 Mini Duos - Specifications | publisher=DeviceSpecifications.com}}</ref>) processor with 1.5&nbsp;[[Gibibyte|GB]] of [[Random-access memory|RAM]] (of which approximately 277 MB is reserved for the system), 16&nbsp;GB of expandable storage, and a 4.5&nbsp;inch (1280x720 pixel) [[HD Super AMOLED]] screen with a [[pixel density]] of 326&nbsp;PPI. The S5 Mini also includes a 2.1-[[megapixel]] front-facing camera, and an 8-megapixel rear-facing camera.\n\nBelow the screen are three buttons. The physical \"Home\" button in the centre contains a swipe-based [[fingerprint reader]]. The \"Recent apps\" and \"Back\" buttons are capacitive. The S5 mini no longer uses a \"Menu\" key like its predecessors.\n\nThe Galaxy S5 Mini comes with Android 4.4.2 Kitkat and Samsung's [[TouchWiz]] software which includes almost all of the features of the S5.\n\nThe S5 Mini contains a 2100 mAh, NFC-enabled battery. Its software, like the S5, also contains an \"Ultra Power Saving\" mode to further extend battery life; when enabled, all non-essential processes are disabled, and the screen switches to only rendering in white on black.  Additional power efficiency features include R2 Semiconductor's [[envelope tracking]] to improve power amplifier efficiency thereby decreasing heat and increasing battery life.<ref name=tr1402>\"[https://www.ifixit.com/Teardown/Samsung+Galaxy+S5+Mini+Teardown/27579 Samsung Galaxy S5 Mini Teardown]\". [[iFixit]]. Retrieved 4 Sept 2014</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Comparison of Samsung Galaxy S smartphones]]\n* [[Samsung Galaxy S series]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|https://www.samsung.com/uk/consumer/mobile-devices/smartphones/android/SM-G800FZKABTU}}\n* [https://forum.xda-developers.com/galaxy-s4/help/guide-tutorial-samsung-galaxy-s4-i9505-t3517706 Howto install Android 9 Pie on Samsung Galaxy S5 mini G800F (aka kminilte with Exynos chip)]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Succession box\n | title  = Samsung Galaxy S5 Mini\n | years  = 2014\n | before = [[Samsung Galaxy S4 Mini]]\n | after  = no successor\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Samsung smartphone}}\n{{Samsung phones}}\n{{Galaxy S}}\n{{Android smartphones}}\n\n[[Category:Android (operating system) devices]]\n[[Category:Samsung mobile phones]]\n[[Category:Samsung Galaxy]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones introduced in 2014]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox mobile phone\n| name          = Samsung Galaxy S5 Mini\n| modelnumber   = SM-G800A, SM-G800F, SM-G800H, SM-G800H/DS, SM-G800M, SM-G800Y, SM-G800R4<ref name=\"sm-g800r4\">{{cite web | url=https://www.samsung.com/us/mobile/cell-phones/SM-G800RZKAUSC-specs | title=Samsung Galaxy S5 Mini - Specifications | publisher=samsung.com}}</ref>\n| logo          = [[File:Samsung Galaxy S5 Mini logo.svg|250px]]\n| logosize      = \n| image         = Samsung Galaxy S5 mini.png\n| imagesize     = 150px\n| caption       = Galaxy S5 Mini in Shimmery White\n| brand         = \n| manufacturer  = [[Samsung Electronics]]\n| slogan        = \n| series        = [[Samsung Galaxy|Galaxy]]\n| networks      = ([[GSM]]/[[GPRS]]/[[EDGE]]): 850, 900, 1,800 and 1,900&nbsp;MHz; <br />[[3G]] ([[HSDPA]] 42.2&nbsp;Mbit/s, [[HSUPA]] 5.76&nbsp;Mbit/s): 850, 900, 1,900 and 2,100&nbsp;MHz; <br /> [[LTE (telecommunication)|LTE]]: 800, 850, 900, 1,800, 2,100 and 2,600&nbsp;MHz\n| released      = {{Start date and age|2014|07|df=yes|br=yes}}\n| continues  = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| status        = \n| unitssold     = \n| unitsshipped  = \n| predecessor   = [[Samsung Galaxy S4 Mini]]\n| successor     = [[Samsung Galaxy Alpha]]\n| related       = [[Samsung Galaxy S5]]<br />[[Samsung Galaxy Alpha]]\n| type          = [[Slate phone|Touchscreen]] [[smartphone]]\n| form          = [[Slate phone|Slate]]\n| size          = {{convert|131.1|mm|in|abbr=on}}&nbsp;H<br />{{convert|64.8|mm|in|abbr=on}}&nbsp;W<br />{{convert|9.1|mm|in|abbr=on}}&nbsp;D\n| weight        = {{convert|120|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| os            = '''Original:''' [[Android (operating system)|Android]] [[Android KitKat|4.4.2 